    "title": "U.S. state attorneys general sue Purdue Pharma over opioid epidemic",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "NEW YORK, May 15 (Reuters) - Several U.S. state attorneys general on Tuesday announced lawsuits against OxyContin maker Purdue Pharma LP, accusing the company of fueling a national opioid epidemic by deceptively marketing prescription painkillers to generate billions of dollars in sales.\nThe attorneys general of Nevada, Texas, Florida, North Carolina, North Dakota and Tennessee separately said the company had violated state consumer protection laws by falsely denying or downplaying the risk of addiction while overstating the benefits of opioids.\nReporting by Tina Bellon; Editing by Bernadette Baum\nOur Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles. ",
